{
  "texts": [
    "As mentioned above, MSSC is a function semantic checking method that aims to mitigate the semantic changes caused by LLM responses.",
    "We evaluate its performance by the following two main metrics.",
    "The first is accuracy, reflecting how many cases MSSC can review correctly.",
    "It is calculated by dividing the number of cases correctly analyzed using MSSC by the total number of cases.",
    "The second is the recall rate, which reflects how many problematic cases MSSC can report among all problematic cases of LLM."
  ]
}